<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="6.[264,1324,997,1903]" box="[264,1118,997,1023]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Material examined: Many parthenogenetic females from Silvituc lagoon.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[264,1324,997,1903]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Body 0.60–0.70 mm, elongate. Head small, slightly directed downward. Second antenna almost reaching posterior margin of valves (
<figureCitation box="[880,952,1077,1103]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 8" captionStartId="7.[264,382,1258,1282]" captionTargetBox="[353,1254,340,1230]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[254,1313,289,1250]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 8. Diaphanosoma bergamini, parthenogenetic female from La Esperanza 1 lagoon; 2) Lateral view; 3) Ventral flap and posterior margin of valves; 4) Spine on dorsal side near posterior margin of valve; 5) Second antenna, lateral view; 6) Distal part of basal segment of A 2; 7) Distal side of first segment of upper 2 ­ segmented branch; 8) Postabdomen and claws." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/171672/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[935,952,1077,1103]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
). Ventral margin of valves with a wide inflexion, armed with several thin setae (
<figureCitation box="[840,912,1117,1143]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 8" captionStartId="7.[264,382,1258,1282]" captionTargetBox="[353,1254,340,1230]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[254,1313,289,1250]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 8. Diaphanosoma bergamini, parthenogenetic female from La Esperanza 1 lagoon; 2) Lateral view; 3) Ventral flap and posterior margin of valves; 4) Spine on dorsal side near posterior margin of valve; 5) Second antenna, lateral view; 6) Distal part of basal segment of A 2; 7) Distal side of first segment of upper 2 ­ segmented branch; 8) Postabdomen and claws." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/171672/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[896,912,1117,1143]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
). A dorsal spine with long setules near posterior margin of valves (
<figureCitation box="[642,714,1157,1183]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 8" captionStartId="7.[264,382,1258,1282]" captionTargetBox="[353,1254,340,1230]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[254,1313,289,1250]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 8. Diaphanosoma bergamini, parthenogenetic female from La Esperanza 1 lagoon; 2) Lateral view; 3) Ventral flap and posterior margin of valves; 4) Spine on dorsal side near posterior margin of valve; 5) Second antenna, lateral view; 6) Distal part of basal segment of A 2; 7) Distal side of first segment of upper 2 ­ segmented branch; 8) Postabdomen and claws." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/171672/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[696,714,1157,1183]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
). Antennal setae 
<number box="[913,959,1157,1183]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="5.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="4.0">4–7</number>
/ 
<number box="[969,1009,1157,1183]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="0.5" valueMax="1.0" valueMin="0.0">0–1</number>
– 
<number box="[1026,1041,1157,1183]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="4.0">4</number>
, spines 
<number box="[1132,1142,1157,1183]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1.0">1</number>
– 
<number box="[1161,1171,1157,1183]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[1183,1228,1157,1183]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="0.5" valueMax="1.0" valueMin="0.0">0–1</number>
– 
<number box="[1247,1257,1157,1183]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1.0">1</number>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 8" captionStartId="7.[264,382,1258,1282]" captionTargetBox="[353,1254,340,1230]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[254,1313,289,1250]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 8. Diaphanosoma bergamini, parthenogenetic female from La Esperanza 1 lagoon; 2) Lateral view; 3) Ventral flap and posterior margin of valves; 4) Spine on dorsal side near posterior margin of valve; 5) Second antenna, lateral view; 6) Distal part of basal segment of A 2; 7) Distal side of first segment of upper 2 ­ segmented branch; 8) Postabdomen and claws." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/171672/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[264,281,1197,1223]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
). Rows of fine spinules on lateral side of postabdomen. Postabdominal claws armed laterally with two rows of fine denticles (
<figureCitation box="[751,821,1237,1263]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 8" captionStartId="7.[264,382,1258,1282]" captionTargetBox="[353,1254,340,1230]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[254,1313,289,1250]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 8. Diaphanosoma bergamini, parthenogenetic female from La Esperanza 1 lagoon; 2) Lateral view; 3) Ventral flap and posterior margin of valves; 4) Spine on dorsal side near posterior margin of valve; 5) Second antenna, lateral view; 6) Distal part of basal segment of A 2; 7) Distal side of first segment of upper 2 ­ segmented branch; 8) Postabdomen and claws." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/171672/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[806,821,1237,1263]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
) and three long spines on the base, two of them wavy.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="6.[264,1324,997,1903]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicName box="[312,622,1317,1342]" class="Branchiopoda" genus="Diaphanosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bergamini">
<emphasis box="[312,622,1317,1342]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Diaphanosoma bergamini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from the Amazon and Orinoco basins in 
<collectingCountry box="[264,384,1357,1383]" name="Venezuela" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
(Paggi &amp; da 
<bibRefCitation author="Rocha" box="[541,693,1357,1383]" pageId="6" pageNumber="26" refString="Paggi, J. C. &amp; da Rocha, C. E. F. (1999) Neodiaphanosoma a new genus of Sididae (Branchiopoda, Ctenopoda); with description of N. bergamini sp n. and comments on N. volzi (Stingelin 1905). Hydrobiologia, 397, 5 - 19." type="journal article" year="1999">
Rocha, 
<number box="[631,693,1357,1383]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1999.0">1999</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), under the generic name 
<emphasis box="[998,1217,1357,1382]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Neodiaphanosoma</emphasis>
Paggi &amp; da 
<bibRefCitation author="Rocha" box="[302,456,1397,1423]" pageId="6" pageNumber="26" refString="Paggi, J. C. &amp; da Rocha, C. E. F. (1999) Neodiaphanosoma a new genus of Sididae (Branchiopoda, Ctenopoda); with description of N. bergamini sp n. and comments on N. volzi (Stingelin 1905). Hydrobiologia, 397, 5 - 19." type="journal article" year="1999">
Rocha, 
<number box="[394,456,1397,1423]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1999.0">1999</number>
</bibRefCitation>
. This genus was based on a numerical phenetic analysis, and supported mainly by the presence of a long finger­like sensillum at the tip of two­segmented antennal branch (
<figureCitation box="[362,437,1477,1503]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 8" captionStartId="7.[264,382,1258,1282]" captionTargetBox="[353,1254,340,1230]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[254,1313,289,1250]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 8. Diaphanosoma bergamini, parthenogenetic female from La Esperanza 1 lagoon; 2) Lateral view; 3) Ventral flap and posterior margin of valves; 4) Spine on dorsal side near posterior margin of valve; 5) Second antenna, lateral view; 6) Distal part of basal segment of A 2; 7) Distal side of first segment of upper 2 ­ segmented branch; 8) Postabdomen and claws." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/171672/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[420,437,1477,1503]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
, arrow). However, we agree with 
<bibRefCitation author="Korovchinsky" box="[851,1105,1477,1503]" pageId="6" pageNumber="25" refString="Korovchinsky, N. M. (2004) Ctenopoda of the World fauna, KMK, Moscow, 410 p. [in Russian]." type="book" year="2004">
Korovchinsky (
<number box="[1036,1098,1477,1503]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="2004.0">2004</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
that separation of the genus 
<emphasis box="[381,601,1517,1542]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Neodiaphanosoma</emphasis>
is not justified, because all characters proposed to support the genus 
<emphasis box="[340,560,1557,1582]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Neodiaphanosoma</emphasis>
are present in other species of the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[1043,1222,1557,1582]" class="Branchiopoda" genus="Diaphanosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1043,1222,1557,1582]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Diaphanosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and the only specific feature is the presence of the finger­like seta.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[264,1324,997,1903]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Silvituc is the northernmost locality of this rare species, which is closely related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Stingelin" authorityName="Stingelin" box="[264,631,1677,1703]" class="Branchiopoda" genus="Diaphanosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="volzi">
<emphasis box="[264,512,1677,1702]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Diaphanosoma volzi</emphasis>
Stingelin
</taxonomicName>
from the Old World. According to Paggi &amp; da 
<bibRefCitation author="Rocha" pageId="6" pageNumber="26" refString="Paggi, J. C. &amp; da Rocha, C. E. F. (1999) Neodiaphanosoma a new genus of Sididae (Branchiopoda, Ctenopoda); with description of N. bergamini sp n. and comments on N. volzi (Stingelin 1905). Hydrobiologia, 397, 5 - 19." type="journal article" year="1999">
Rocha (
<number box="[273,336,1717,1743]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1999.0">1999</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, both taxa have restricted their distribution to the tropics and subtropics, but apparently some other unknown factors limit their distribution inside this geographical range, at least for 
<taxonomicName box="[482,639,1797,1822]" class="Branchiopoda" genus="Diaphanosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bergamini">
<emphasis box="[482,639,1797,1822]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">D. bergamini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, since we have not detected it in any other system in the studied region. It was co­existing with 
<taxonomicName authority="Sars" authorityName="Sars" box="[761,1137,1837,1863]" class="Branchiopoda" genus="Diaphanosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevireme">
<emphasis box="[761,1071,1837,1862]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Diaphanosoma brevireme</emphasis>
Sars
</taxonomicName>
, a much more common species in this area.
</paragraph>
